Resource allocations made in the context of a national food control system may, dependant on the above be attributed to: 
• Training and basic infrastructure; 
• Suitably qualified personnel of relevant disciplinary backgrounds 
• Reliable transportation systems and equipment to perform inspection, audit and verification services and transmission of samples to laboratories; and 
• Information, communication and technology (ICT) systems;
The design of a national food control system should incorporate timely access to adequate information relating to the surveillance, investigation and response to food borne illness and food related incidents.
